			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Contaminated soil refers to the presence of toxic chemicals in soil that exceed naturally occurring levels and pose risks to human health and the environment. These contaminants can leach into ground or surface waters, be taken up by plants and animals, contaminate drinking water supplies, or volatilize and affect indoor air quality. Soil contamination can result from pesticides, petroleum products, asbestos, lead, and other hazardous substances. It can be localized or widespread, affecting soil's ability to support plant growth, provide nutrients, and regulate water and air quality. The EPA aims to prevent adverse effects by protecting soil integrity, while the FAO highlights soil contamination as a global concern, with one-third of the world's soil already severely or moderately degraded.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">污染土壤是指土壤中存在的有毒化学物质超过了自然水平，对人类健康和环境构成风险。这些污染物可能渗入地下水或地表水，被动植物吸收，污染饮用水供应，或挥发并影响室内空气质量。土壤污染可能由杀虫剂、石油产品、石棉、铅和其他有害物质引起。它可以是局部的或广泛的，影响土壤支持植物生长、提供营养以及调节水和空气质量的能力。环境保护署旨在通过保护土壤完整性来防止不利影响，而粮农组织则强调土壤污染是全球关注的问题，世界上三分之一的土壤已经严重或中度退化。</common:generalComment>
